    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
      <![CDATA[<pre>[Congressional Record Volume 167, Number 168 (Monday, September 27, 2021)][House]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href="https://www.gpo.gov">www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. GOHMERT:H.R. 5379.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article I, Section 9, Clause 7 of the U.S. Constitutionsets forth the power of appropriations and states that ``NoMoney shall be drawn from the Treasury but in Consequence ofAppropriations made by Law. . . . ''In addition, Article I, Section 8, Clause 1 states that``The Congress shall have the Power . . . to pay the Debtsand provide for the common Defense and general Welfare of theUnited States. . . .''Also, Article I, Section 8, Clauses 12 and 13 states thatCongress shall have power ``to raise and support Armies . ..'' and ``to provide and maintain a Navy.''[Page H5463]</pre>]]>
    </constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
